The paper deals with the theoretical performance limits of a multicell Massive MIMO network, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communication (cs.COM). The paper discusses the achievable rates in the uplink and downlink, assuming single-cell linear processing and uncorrelated MIMO Rician fading channel matrix. The analysis is conducted assuming that $N$ and $K$ grow large with a given ratio $N/K$, which is a typical assumption in information theory and signal processing. The paper also considers the impact of LoS components, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
